        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-09-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-09-26T20:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <head>473. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Laos</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d473fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751J.00/9–2757. Top Secret. Repeated to Paris, London, Bangkok,
                        Saigon, and Phnom Penh.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vientiane</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-09-27T08:00:00+07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1957—8 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>475. Reference <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 460.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d473fn2">In telegram 460 from Vientiane, September 25, the Embassy
                        provided a “round up of the political scene, particularly the Pathet Lao
                        problem.” (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, 751J.00/9–2557)</note> …
                    instructions from Hanoi to <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> Delegation here
                    some … days ago, burden of which was: (1) take generally conciliatory attitude
                    (2) avoid creating situation which would embarrass <persName corresp="#p_SP2"
                        >Souvanna</persName> or undermine his authority. … this confirms story of
                    his belief <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> are fearful that failure to make
                    satisfactory [progress?] in political negotiations by October 9 may result in
                    formation new government under <persName corresp="#p_KDS1">Katay</persName>. He
                    claimed also to have information that <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>
                    authorities at Sam Neua prepared to be even more conciliatory than current
                    instructions to <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> delegation imply. <pb
                        facs="1012" n="978" xml:id="pg_978"/> He ascribed this development to
                    worsening economic and political situation in both North Vietnam and Mainland
                    China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLL1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Bacon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
